                        "immortality, then shall come to pass the saying that is written: Death is swallowed "
                        "up in victory' (15:54, quoting Isaiah 25:8). Paul then taunts the defeated enemy with "
                        "Hosea 13:14: 'O death, where is your victory? O death, where is your sting?' (15:55). "
                        "The sting (kentron) of death is sin -- sin gives death its power to condemn. The power "
